# memdog

Personal memory platform that ingests, stores, enriches, and queries arbitrary data from 25+ communication channels through AI-powered processing.

## What It Does

- **Ingest** data from WhatsApp, Telegram, Slack, Discord, Signal, Matrix, email, and 18+ more channels — or upload directly via the web UI (text, files, URLs, camera, voice, video)
- **Store** any data type with automatic versioning, tags, per-item access control, and memory containers (timeline, session, conversation, factual, episodic, semantic, custom)
- **Enrich** every piece of data through a 40-agent AI pipeline that classifies content, generates analysis viewpoints, and creates vector embeddings
- **Query** across all stored data using conversational RAG chat with inline citations, semantic similarity search, or structured API queries

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    Channels["Channels\nWhatsApp, Telegram, Slack, ..."] --> OC["Webhook Gateway\n+ OpenClaw Node"]
    Users --> UI["UI\nNext.js"]

    OC --> Pipeline["Webhook Pipeline\nNATS + 40 typed agents"]
    OC --> API["API\nFastAPI"]
    UI --> API
    API -- callbacks --> Pipeline
    Pipeline -- stores data --> API

    API --> Storage["Storage\nGCS / Supabase / local"]
```

| Component | Stack | Deployment |
|-----------|-------|------------|
| **API** | Python 3.12, FastAPI | GKE |
| **UI** | Next.js 14, React 18, TypeScript | Cloud Run |
| **Webhook Pipeline** | Python 3.12, FastAPI, NATS | GKE |
| **Webhook Gateway** | Python 3.12, FastAPI | GKE |
| **OpenClaw Node** | Node.js (OpenClaw runtime) | GKE |
| **Python Client** | Python, httpx | pip install |

## Quick Start

```bash
# Start the full local stack (9 services)
docker compose up

# UI:       http://localhost:3000
# API:      http://localhost:8080
# API docs: http://localhost:8080/docs
# Gateway:  http://localhost:8070/docs
```

## Key Features

### Data & Storage
- Universal storage (JSON, text, binary, images, files)
- Automatic versioning on every update
- Per-item ACLs (public, authenticated, user-specific, role-based)
- 10 memory types (timeline, session, conversation, user, organizational, factual, episodic, semantic, custom, tracing)
- Three storage backends: local filesystem, GCS, Supabase (PostgreSQL + pgvector)

### AI Pipeline
- 40 typed sub-agents for images, PDFs, code, JSON, audio, video, medical records, geospatial data, and more
- 6-layer data classification (explicit field → LLM classifier → MIME → URL extension → fallback)
- Tiered model routing: small (gemma3:4b), medium (12b), large (27b), multimodal (qwen3-vl), omni (qwen3.5)
- Per-user, per-data-type model overrides with smart routing
- Customizable agent pipeline configs (intro, system prompt, output schema, skills, model tier)
- Vector embeddings (pgvector) and RAG chat with inline citations
- **Graph memory** — automatic entity/relationship extraction into Postgres (person, org, product, location, concept, event), entity-aware RAG search
- **Memory compression** — LLM-powered summarization of verbose memories, auto-triggers at configurable thresholds

### Developer SDK
- **Simple SDK** — `MemDog` facade with 8 methods: `add()`, `search()`, `get()`, `delete()`, `entities()`, `related()`, `compress()`
- **Agent adapters** — drop-in memory backends for LangChain (`ChatMessageHistory` + `Retriever`), CrewAI (`save/search`), and OpenAI function calling
- **Full REST client** — 70+ methods covering all API endpoints

### Multi-Channel Ingestion
- 25+ channels with DigiMe AI agent for querying the RAG system
- 300-provider integration platform with OAuth2, API-key auth, and credential-injecting API proxy

### Observability
- OpenTelemetry distributed tracing across all components
- Waterfall span viewer in the UI
- Per-user stats with LLM token usage breakdowns

## Project Structure

```
memdog/
├── api/                  # Core API (FastAPI, Python 3.12)
├── ui/                   # Web frontend (Next.js 14, TypeScript)
├── webhook/              # Data processing pipeline
│   ├── receiver/         #   HTTP receiver (Flask)
│   ├── processor/        #   NATS pull worker
│   └── webhook_agent/    #   Agent server + 40 sub-agents
├── webhook-gateway/      # Multi-channel webhook gateway
├── openclaw-node/        # DigiMe AI agent (queries memdog RAG system)
├── client/               # Python SDK
├── mcp-server/           # MCP server
├── k8s/                  # Kubernetes manifests
│   ├── *.yaml            #   API + UI (memdog namespace)
│   ├── webhook-pipeline/ #   NATS + agents + Ollama
│   ├── webhook-gateway/  #   Gateway + load balancer
│   ├── openclaw-node/    #   DigiMe AI agent
│   └── supabase/         #   Self-hosted Supabase stack
├── scripts/              # Deploy, test, and utility scripts
├── config/               # Shared AI model config (ai.env)
├── testing/              # E2E tests (Playwright)
├── docker-compose.yml    # Local dev (9 services)
└── skaffold.yaml         # K8s local dev
```

## Deployment

```bash
# API → GKE
GKE_CLUSTER=open-jaw GKE_ZONE=us-central1-a \
  ./scripts/manual-deploy.sh deploy-api-gke -p memdog-dev -e dev

# UI → Cloud Run
./scripts/manual-deploy.sh deploy-ui -p memdog-dev -e dev

# Webhook Pipeline → GKE
GKE_CLUSTER=open-jaw GKE_ZONE=us-central1-a \
  ./scripts/manual-deploy.sh deploy-webhook-pipeline-gke -p memdog-dev -e dev
```

## API

60+ REST endpoints across data, memories, users, tags, versions, AI query, embeddings, viewpoints, prompts, skills, channels, stats, and bulk operations.

```bash
# Create data
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/data \
  -F "content=Hello world" -F "name=greeting"

# Query with AI
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/ai/query/chat \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"query": "What do I know about meetings?", "user_id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001"}'

# Semantic search
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/ai/query/semantic \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"query": "project updates", "limit": 5}'
```

